                <h3 class="card-title">Fat Loss Workout Plan</h3>
                <pre>
1. Full-Body Strength Training (3 Days per Week)
Strength training helps preserve muscle mass while you're in a calorie deficit, which is crucial for keeping your metabolism high.

Day 1: Full-Body Strength Training
- Squats (Barbell or Dumbbell) – 4 sets of 12–15 reps
- Push-Ups or Chest Press – 4 sets of 10–12 reps
- Dumbbell Rows or Barbell Rows – 4 sets of 10–12 reps
- Lunges (Bodyweight or Dumbbell) – 3 sets of 12 reps per leg
- Dumbbell Shoulder Press – 3 sets of 12–15 reps
- Plank – 3 sets, hold for 30–60 seconds

Day 2: Full-Body Circuit
Perform each exercise in a circuit, resting for 30–45 seconds between each. Repeat for 3-4 rounds.
- Jump Squats – 20 reps
- Push-Ups – 15 reps
- Renegade Rows (with Dumbbells) – 12 reps per side
- Burpees – 12 reps
- Mountain Climbers – 20 reps per leg
- Russian Twists – 20 reps per side
        </pre>

                <h3 class="mt-4">2. High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT)</h3>
                <pre>
2–3 Days per Week
HIIT boosts metabolism and burns fat while preserving muscle.

HIIT Workout Example (30 Minutes):
- Warm-Up (5 minutes): Light cardio (jogging, cycling, etc.)
- Workout (20 minutes): 
  30 seconds sprinting + 1 minute walking/jogging
  Repeat for 20 minutes
- Cool-Down (5 minutes): Stretching or light walking

Alternative HIIT Circuit:
- Jumping Jacks – 30 seconds
- Burpees – 30 seconds
- High Knees – 30 seconds
- Mountain Climbers – 30 seconds
- Rest 1 minute, repeat for 3-5 rounds
        </pre>

                <h3 class="mt-4">3. Steady-State Cardio (Optional)</h3>
                <pre>
1–2 Days per Week
Examples: Jogging, cycling, rowing, brisk walking

Duration: 30–45 minutes at 60–70% of your max heart rate
(Able to hold a conversation, but still working up a sweat)
        </pre>

                <h3 class="mt-4">4. Core Exercises (2–3 Days per Week)</h3>
                <pre>
- Plank – 3 sets, hold for 30–60 seconds
- Russian Twists – 3 sets of 20 reps per side
- Leg Raises – 3 sets of 12–15 reps
- Bicycle Crunches – 3 sets of 20 reps
- Mountain Climbers – 3 sets of 20 reps per leg
- Flutter Kicks – 3 sets of 30 seconds
        </pre>

                <h3 class="mt-4">Additional Tips for Fat Loss</h3>

                <h5 class="mt-3">1. Nutrition</h5>
                <pre>
- Calorie Deficit: Burn more calories than you consume. Aim for a 300–500 calorie deficit.
- Protein: 1.6–2.2g per kg of body weight daily.
- Include healthy fats (avocados, nuts, olive oil) and complex carbs (whole grains, fruits, vegetables).
        </pre>

                <h5 class="mt-3">2. Hydration</h5>
                <pre>
- Drink at least 8 cups (2 liters) of water per day
- Increase intake during workouts or hot weather
        </pre>

                <h5 class="mt-3">3. Sleep & Recovery</h5>
                <pre>
- Aim for 7–8 hours of sleep per night
- Crucial for muscle repair, hormones, and workout recovery
        </pre>

                <h5 class="mt-3">4. Consistency</h5>
                <pre>
- Stick to your plan, stay patient, and stay consistent.
- Fat loss is gradual — give your body time to adapt and progress.
        </pre>
